value.title: Nebraska Gov. Ricketts sending police to Texas because Biden is 'failing so miserably' at southern border
value.excerpt: Nebraska Republican Gov. Pete Ricketts told "Your World" on Tuesday that he has dispatched state troopers to assist the Texas Department of Public Safety because President Joe Biden “failing so miserably” at the southern border.

value.title: GOP senators tear into Biden national security adviser for calling Nord Stream 2 AG a 'Swiss' company
value.excerpt: The senators blasted National Security Adviser Jake Sullivan for his Sunday interview where he was pressed on the Biden administration waiving sanctions on the Nord Stream 2 pipeline, which would give Russia greater influence in Europe.

value.title: Obama ethics chief: Hunter Biden selling art at 'obviously inflated prices' to mystery buyers feels 'grifty'
value.excerpt: Walter Shaub, the former Office of Government Ethics director under Obama, ripped into Biden for selling his art for up to $500,000, saying that, while the issue would not involve his governmental alma mater, “common sense should have steered him away from this sale.”

value.title: DeSantis edges out Trump in 2024 straw poll, Tucker Carlson rules out bid
value.excerpt: Ron DeSantis, who has endeared himself to conservatives for bucking coronavirus restrictions and lockdowns, and combating critical race theory, hasn’t said he would mount a campaign in 2024.

value.title: Republicans slam Biden's 'vague threats' to China over COVID stonewall
value.excerpt: House Republicans are not satisfied with the Biden administration’s stance against the Chinese government when it comes to making sure there is a thorough investigation of the coronavirus pandemic.

value.title: Biden nominee with CRT ties appears headed for close party-line vote
value.excerpt: President Biden's nominee to run the Office of Personnel Management (OPM) appears to be headed for a close, party-line vote in the Senate this week amid Republican concerns about her past ties to critical race theory and Ibram X. Kendi.

value.title: Iran's president-elect won’t meet Biden, demands US ‘lift all oppressive sanctions’
value.excerpt: Iran's president-elect said Monday he wouldn't meet with President Joe Biden nor negotiate over Tehran's ballistic missile program and its support of regional militias, sticking to a hardline position following his landslide victory in last week's election.

value.title: Trump wishes a happy Father’s Day to ‘losers’ and ‘RINOs’
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump on Sunday sent a Father’s Day message to his political adversaries — who he blasted as “losers.”

value.title: Nina Simone's grandaughter says Kamala Harris 'bullied' her mother to the point she 'almost killed herself'
value.excerpt: Legendary singer Nina Simone’s granddaughter accused Vice President Harris of causing the family to lose control of Simone's estate.

value.title: WaPo knocked for painting Biden as 'deeply Catholic' in debate over Communion: 'Clueless'
value.excerpt: Critics unloaded on The Washington Post for publishing a piece that described President Biden as "deeply Catholic" in its analysis of the debate over whether the president should continue to take Communion in light of his support of some abortion policies.

value.title: Judge Jeanine says Joe Biden is a 'puppet'; says Putin would have 'mopped the floor with him'
value.excerpt: Jeanine Pirro slammed Joe Biden Saturday on “Justice with Judge Jeanine” for being a “puppet” in the White House, asking who was really “pulling the strings.”

value.title: Trump supporter sues town for $25M: ‘They’re trying to silence me’

value.title: Bidens announce death of family dog Champ, 'our sweet, good boy'
value.excerpt: President Biden and First Lady Jill Biden on Saturday announced the death of Champ, one of their two German shepherds, describing him as a "cherished companion" and a "sweet, good boy."

value.title: WV AG Morrisey sounds alarm on fentanyl overdose surge, points to Biden border policies
value.excerpt: West Virginia Attorney General Patrick Morrisey believes President Biden's decision to reverse the Trump administration's "remain in Mexico" policy has led to a spike in fentanyl trafficking and overdoses within the U.S.

value.title: Dem blasts Biden's decision to extend Canadian border restrictions another month: 'bulls---'
value.excerpt: New York lawmakers are irate over the White House’s decision to renew the Canada border shutdown for yet another month.

value.title: Trump endorses Murkowski primary opponent Kelly Tshibaka
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump endorsed the primary opponent to Sen. Lisa Murkowski on Friday, declaring his support for Kelly Tshibaka Alaska's former commissioner of administration.

value.title: Cruz rips Kamala Harris for avoiding border trip on 'Fox & Friends': Like a ‘comedy show’
value.excerpt: Ted Cruz, R- Texas, slammed the Biden administration for its inaction at the southern border on " Fox & Friends " Friday. Sen. Cruz said Vice President Kamala Harris ' failure to visit the border and avoidance of the topic is becoming like "a comedy show.

value.title: Biden's 'off-limits' list for Russian cyberattacks criticized as 'green light' to target everything else
value.excerpt: President Biden's list of 16 key infrastructure entities that are “off-limits” to Russian cyberattacks has effectively given the Russians a green light to target everything not on that list without facing serious repercussions, national security experts and senior Republicans tell Fox News.

value.title: Dr. Ronny Jackson calls on Biden to immediately undergo cognitive test to assess 'mental impairment'
value.excerpt: Dr. Ronny Jackson, the former White House physician, called on President Biden to immediately undergo a cognitive test so the commander-in-chief can prove to the American public sound mental capabilities.

value.title: Kushner snags book deal with Harper Collins; no deal yet for Trump
value.excerpt: The Broadside Books imprint of Harper Collins said it signed Donald Trump’s son-in-law and former trusted adviser to a book that’s still untitled but apparently well underway and

value.title: Axios mocked for blaming worker burnout on Capitol riot, 'fallout from the Trump presidency'
value.excerpt: Many Americans have declined to return to work following coronavirus shutdowns and enhanced unemployment benefits, but Axios feels the labor shortage is largely former President Donald Trump’s fault.

value.title: Arizona sheriff says 'no distinct' border changes from Biden administration despite Sec. Mayorkas meetings
value.excerpt: An Arizona sheriff says there have been no changes in policy, messaging or results from the Biden administration on the crisis at the southern border -- despite multiple meetings between sheriffs and Homeland Security Secretary Alejandro Mayorkas.

value.title: White House cheers Supreme Court ObamaCare decision with nod to Biden's 'big f--- deal' hot mic comment
value.excerpt: The White House cheered the U.S. Supreme Court’s decision to uphold Obamacare, with a nod at President Biden’s 2010 “big f**king deal” reaction to then-President Obama signing the Affordable Care Act into law.

value.title: Lara Trump rips Biden for only taking questions from pre-approved reporters: 'Are you kidding me?'
value.excerpt: Fox News contributor Lara Trump tore into President Biden on Thursday for only taking pre-approved questions from reporters during a press conference following his meeting with Putin in Geneva.

value.title: Trump on COVID origins: 'I believe it was a terrible accident, but I believe it came from the lab'
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump said Wednesday that he believes the coronavirus pandemic is the result of a "terrible accident" during an exclusive interview on "Hannity."

value.title: House approves bill marking Juneteenth a federal holiday, sending it to Biden's desk
value.excerpt: The U.S. House of Representatives on Wednesday approved a bill that aims to establish June 19th, or Juneteenth, a federal holiday.

value.title: Biden DOJ drops lawsuit against John Bolton over 2020 book release
value.excerpt: The Justice Department has dropped its civil lawsuit against former National Security Adviser John Bolton over the publication of his 2020 book, “The Room Where It Happened,” according to a court filing obtained by Fox News on Wednesday.

value.title: Merrick Garland reverses Trump-era decisions on asylum claims
value.excerpt: The Department of Justice (DOJ) announced the reversals on Wednesday, which would set U.S. immigration policy back to where it was before decisions made by Trump-era DOJ officials Attorney General Jeff Sessions and Deputy Attorney General Jeffrey Rosen.

value.title: Hillary Clinton pushes narrative that Putin ‘helped elect’ Trump during 2016 election
value.excerpt: Former Secretary of State and failed presidential candidate Hillary Clinton continued to push the narrative that Russian President Vladimir Putin "helped elect" former President Donald Trump on Wednesday.
